definitions.definition: To note the time or place of writing or executing; to express in an instrument the time of its execution.
examples: to date a letter, a bond, a deed, or a charter

definitions.definition: To note or fix the time of (an event); to give the date of.
To determine the age of something.
examples: to date the building of the pyramids

definitions.definition: To take (someone) on a date , or a series of dates.
To have a steady relationship with; to be romantically involved with.
To have a steady relationship with each other; to be romantically involved with each other.
examples: They met a couple of years ago, but have been dating for about five months.

definitions.definition: To make or become old, especially in such a way as to fall out of fashion, become less appealing or attractive, etc.
examples: The comedian dated himself by making quips about bands from the 1960s.

definitions.definition: To have beginning; to begin; to be dated or reckoned.
